comments.body: Why no tests without type arguments? The new code seems to apply exclusively in this case.

[completionsGenericIndexedAccess2](https://github.com/microsoft/TypeScript/pull/34855/files#diff-10da2e23de6b7208e06ed04e2e1770c5) is without type arguments, which tests the primary way that #33937 was a regression. Almost all the existing tests from #33937 / #32100 are without type arguments, but they weren’t complex enough to fail. This test was to ensure that the new clever stuff _doesn’t_ apply when there _is_ an explicit type argument.
